--TASK 2: VERIFY NORMALISATION--
 
-- 1NF ANALYSIS:
-- Every column in every table holds a single atomic value (e.g. first_name and
-- last_name are split rather than one "full_name" field; a single phone_number
-- column, if added, holds one number). A 1NF VIOLATION would occur if we stored
-- multiple phone numbers in one field, e.g. phone_numbers = '9876543210,9988776655'
-- — this is non-atomic and breaks 1NF. We avoid this by giving each value its own
-- column/row (or a separate child table if multiple values are genuinely needed).
 
-- 2NF ANALYSIS:
-- 2NF requires every non-key column to depend on the WHOLE primary key, not just
-- part of it. In our schema, every table uses a single-column surrogate key
-- (student_id, course_id, enrollment_id, etc.), so partial dependency cannot occur.
-- The enrollments table has a *candidate* composite key of (student_id, course_id),
-- but its actual PRIMARY KEY is the surrogate enrollment_id; enrollment_date and
-- grade depend on the full enrollment_id, so 2NF holds. If we had used
-- (student_id, course_id) as the PK instead, grade and enrollment_date would still
-- depend on the whole pair, not on student_id or course_id alone, so 2NF would
-- still be satisfied either way.
 
-- 3NF ANALYSIS:
-- 3NF requires no transitive dependencies (non-key column depending on another
-- non-key column rather than directly on the PK). Storing dept_name directly in
-- the students table WOULD violate 3NF, because dept_name depends on
-- department_id, which depends on student_id (student_id -> department_id ->
-- dept_name is a transitive dependency). Our schema avoids this by keeping
-- dept_name only in the departments table and referencing it via the
-- department_id foreign key from students, courses, and professors.
 
-- 3NF ANALYSIS SPECIFIC TO enrollments:
-- enrollments holds enrollment_id (PK), student_id, course_id, enrollment_date,
-- grade. Both enrollment_date and grade describe the enrollment EVENT itself, not
-- attributes of the student or course, so they depend directly on enrollment_id
-- and not transitively on any other non-key column. No transitive dependency
-- exists; the table satisfies 3NF.



